      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T03:14:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m thinking about how we can make the naming here most clear. In general, this class has two types of fields/properties: those of the full, un-elided tree, and those of the elided version of the tree.\n\nGiven that the former represent the actual underlying data and the latter are computed from the former, perhaps we could keep the former names simple, and add \"elided\" or some similar word to the computed properties?\n\nSo the name changes would be:\nimmediateBranchName-\u003ename\nimmediatePath-\u003epath\nimmediateUnbranchedTests-\u003eunbranchedTests\nimmediateTests-\u003etests\nimmediateChildren-\u003echildren\nbranchName()-\u003eelidedBranchName()\ntests()-\u003eelidedTests()\nchildren()-\u003eelidedChildren()\n\nWhat do you think?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 59,
        "startChar": 19,
        "endLine": 59,
        "endChar": 38
      },
      "revId": "7be934ae7b372f01c37dd5fefbecb10a1272a060",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
